<subSubSection id="4BE74DEB4C4FFFB8FED9FD936B55FCB4" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="03421E604C4FFFB8FED9FD936B55FCB4" blockId="41.[264,1324,625,776]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C4FFFB8FED9FD936E1FFD35" bold="true" box="[264,367,625,649]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks</emphasis>
: No specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="7BEA5EF04C4FFFB8FD82FD936DEBFD34" box="[595,667,625,648]" name="Eritrea" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
were found that matched the characters in Bezzi’s (
<number id="B5350C474C4FFFB8FB6EFD936B86FD34" box="[1215,1270,625,648]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="1924.0">1924</number>
) key for 
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C4FFFB8FE8CFD736EA0FD14" box="[349,464,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Litorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corticea">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C4FFFB8FE8CFD736EA0FD14" box="[349,464,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">L. corticea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but a male specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="7BEA5EF04C4FFFB8FD3EFD736C57FD14" box="[751,807,657,680]" name="Chad" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Chad</collectingCountry>
did so and was designated 
<typeStatus id="DC46A0C24C4FFFB8FB99FD736BECFD14" box="[1096,1180,657,680]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">neotype</typeStatus>
in Greathead (
<number id="B5350C474C4FFFB8FE91FD536E0AFD74" box="[320,378,689,712]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="1967.0">1967</number>
). The 
<typeStatus id="DC46A0C24C4FFFB8FE6CFD536D61FD74" box="[445,529,689,712]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">neotype</typeStatus>
specimen was described and the genitalia were illustrated. Bezzi’s (
<number id="B5350C474C4FFFB8FB3DFD536A53FD74" box="[1260,1315,689,712]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="1924.0">1924</number>
) 
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C4FFFB8FEE9FD336EDCFD54" box="[312,428,721,744]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Litorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corticea">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C4FFFB8FEE9FD336EDCFD54" box="[312,428,721,744]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">L. corticea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C4FFFB8FE65FD336D38FD54" box="[436,584,721,744]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="variety" variety="corticalis">
var. 
<emphasis id="3189C2724C4FFFB8FE32FD336D38FD54" box="[483,584,721,744]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">corticalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a male from 
<collectingCountry id="7BEA5EF04C4FFFB8FC62FD336B61FD54" box="[947,1041,721,744]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
. The female from 
<collectingCountry id="7BEA5EF04C4FFFB8FB09FD336A5BFD54" box="[1240,1323,721,744]" name="Uganda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Uganda</collectingCountry>
originally identified as 
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C4FFFB8FDE1FD136DD3FCB4" box="[560,675,753,776]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Litorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corticea">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C4FFFB8FDE1FD136DD3FCB4" box="[560,675,753,776]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">L. corticea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C4FFFB8FD7BFD136C4DFCB4" box="[682,829,753,776]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="variety" variety="corticalis">
var. 
<emphasis id="3189C2724C4FFFB8FD09FD136C4DFCB4" box="[728,829,753,776]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">corticalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a different species.
</paragraph>
